name: SINGA AMBARA RAJA
description:
#MaskSeries : Singa Ambara Raja

Singa Ambara Raja is a mythological animal that symbolizes the glory of the city of Singaraja, Bali. The Lion Ambara Raja is positioned to grip the corn kernels which means strength, power, and the figure of the knight Ki Gusti Ngurah Panji Sakti who became King of Buleleng in the past.
